Paper: hep-th/9902138

Date: 1999-02-19

Title: Towards a Nonperturbative Covariant Regularization in 4D Quantum Field

TheoryAuthors: H. Grosse, A. Strohmaier

Comments: 16 pages, 1 figure

Journal-ref: Lett.Math.Phys. 48 (1999) 163-179

We give a noncommutative version of the complex projective space CP^2 andshow that scalar QFT on this space is free of UV divergencies. The toolsnecessary to investigate Quantum fields on this fuzzy CP^2 are developed andpossibilities to introduce spinors and Dirac operators are discussed.